Option 2

Here you will remove  userdata reference from the Jenkins EC2 resource inside main.tf 

1. Bootstrap Script

Create a file:

nano setup.sh

Paste the content of setup.sh into the file created

2. How to run it
Step 1 — Make executable
chmod +x setup.sh

Step 2 — Run script
./setup.sh
Step 3 — Reconnect (VERY IMPORTANT)

After it finishes:

exit

SSH back in again so Docker permissions apply.

🌐 3. Access your tools
Jenkins
http://<your-ec2-ip>:8080
SonarQube
http://<your-ec2-ip>:9000

Login:

admin / admin

🧠 What this script sets up (clean architecture)

Tool	How it runs

Jenkins	Docker container
SonarQube	Docker container
Trivy	Run in pipeline (container)
Helm	Run in pipeline (container)
kubectl	Installed
AWS CLI	Installed

🔥 Why this is the right approach :

No messy installs
Everything reproducible
Easy to destroy + rebuild
Matches real DevOps workflows